task.summary: I can't believe this thing actually works

Created EchoPlot class(es) - one for userplot and one for plots - to impelment basic echo protocol for debugging purposes. Moved some stuff around and added more sophisticated command line parsing for the spawned process, which is now in a position to be suitable for for use as a standalone plot server.
Need to begin refactoring into proper desired architecture, including turning the spawned process into a *server* rather than a client by default.

Created EchoPlot class(es) - one for userplot and one for plots - to impelment basic echo protocol for debugging purposes. Moved some stuff around and added more sophisticated command line parsing for the spawned process, which is now in a position to be suitable for for use as a standalone plot server.
Need to begin refactoring into proper desired architecture, including turning the spawned process into a *server* rather than a client by default.

Slight restructuring of manager, including initialization of protocol instances to allow remove protocol reference to event loop and leave manager in charge. Implemented basic RPC framework on top of existing protocol.

Added animated plot axis labels. Currently solved a label clipping issue by setting ymargin to 0.02, but this looks kind of ugly. Todo: manually scale y axis limits to fix only the top label as needed.
Y axis limits successfully scaled to avoid cutting off top label.
